President Cyril Ramaphosa on Monday night announced former Tshwane mayor Kgosientsho Ramokgopa as the  minister of electricity. Ramokgopa was a senior official in the presidency in charge of infrastructure projects. Ramaphosa also announced ANC deputy president Paul Mashatile as deputy president of the country. The announcement brought to an end speculation who would occupy the newly created post to deal with the electricity crisis. This is a developing story. IN FULL | Newly appointed cabinet ministers TimesLIVE